AB  - This paper summarizes a global assessment of digital agriculture services and their impacts. A scoping review conducted under a protocol aligned to the internationally accepted PRISMA- ScR found that most studies are focused on the provision of digital advisory and extension services to farmers, and they reported outcomes associated mainly with "practice change" and "increased knowledge." While many studies focused on on-farm agronomy, either through digital advisory or precision agriculture tools, they lacked data about outcomes related to environmental sustainability and climate resilience. This review also found that use facilitators and barriers should also be considered when studying and reporting on the uptake of services and their outcomes.
