AB  - Sustainable management of livestock and rangelands faces considerable challenges due to escalating human demands and the impacts of climate change. These elements not only threaten natural resources but also compromise the sustainability of livestock production systems. Therefore, it is essential to implement strategies that enhance environmental performance and secure the long-term sustainability of livestock production. Such initiatives can aid in conserving natural resources and promoting global food security. The present study evaluates and compares various livestock and rangeland management strategies aimed at strengthening the rangelandbased livestock farming system in northern Iran. The main goal of this research is to identify the most effective strategies for sustainable rangeland management and to reduce the negative environmental impacts associated with livestock operations. To achieve this objective, a twostage stochastic programming modeling framework was utilized. A sample of 256 livestock farmers was selected for comprehensive interviews, and the necessary data was gathered at the farm level during a field study conducted in the year 2022. The findings of this study indicate that the adoption of integrated strategies, which include the development of alternative rangeland uses and the alleviation of pressure on rangelands, can significantly enhance the economic conditions of livestock farmers while also safeguarding rangelands. These results provide empirical support for the economic benefits of integrated livestock-rangeland management strategies. To promote sustainable resource management and improve the livelihoods of pastoralists, the implementation of such strategies should be strengthened.
