FX  - This paper forms part of her PhD research on gendered approaches to disaster risk reduction, with focus on climate-smart agriculture adoption by small-holder farmers in disaster-prone regions. This research was supported by the Department of Science and Technology-National Research Foundation (DST-NRF) Centre for Excellence in Food Security. Appreciation goes to the research assistants, farmers, non-government organisations and government departments in Chikwawa and Gwembe who played different roles during the data collection stage of this study.
